Description: toro is an R package that provides a useful interface to the MapLibreGL JS package,
    allowing these maps to be embedded directly into a Shiny web application, and rendering of
    spatial data quickly with many customisable options (clusters, custom icons, map layers and
    backgrounds). The goal of the package is to make it easier to interpret and explore large
    spatial datasets within the context of a Shiny dashboard, without having long loading times
    waiting for a map to update with new data.
